    • createUnifiedList

      public java.util.List<DYModule> createUnifiedList​(java.util.List<DYModule> defaultModules, java.util.List<DYModule> loadedModules)
      Before writing the modules to file we need to unify the defaultModules list with the loadedModules list. Logic: Create a new list, then go thorough the defaultModules list, and check if there is a matching key in the loadedModules list. If there is a match add that module instead, and overwrite its defaultValues and comments. This ensures, that loaded modules which do not exist in the defaultModules list do not get saved to file. Using save() will result in overwriting the file with the current modules. The current modules get their values from the loadedModules.
      Parameters:
      defaultModules -
      loadedModules -
      Returns:
